## Production Best Practices

### 1. Version Control
- Store prompts in `.jinja` template files
- Use semantic versioning (v1.0.0, v1.1.0)
- Document changes in commit messages
- Tag production-ready versions

### 2. Monitoring
- Log all LLM calls with Langfuse/LangSmith
- Track success rate per prompt
- Monitor latency per step
- Alert on elevated error rates

### 3. Guardrails
- Validate output format before returning
- Check score ranges (0.0-1.0)
- Verify required fields present
- Sanitize/escape user inputs

### 4. Cost Management
- Use cheaper models for data collection (GPT-4o-mini)
- Use premium models for analysis/reasoning (GPT-4, Claude Opus)
- Implement caching for repeated queries
- Set token limits per request

### 5. Compliance
- Never store PII in prompts
- Log data lineage for audit trails
- Include disclaimers in outputs
- Respect data licensing restrictions

